The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Thursday, July 21, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, July 20: Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will meet his Jharkhand counterpart Arjun Munda tomorrow and discuss the supply of iron ore for the proposed five million-tonne steel plant by the Jindal Group in Bengal. 

 The two states have been locked in a tussle over iron ore linkage.

 Calcutta: A bomb scare on VIP Road brought traffic to a standstill for half an hour from 9 pm on Wednesday. The police officer on duty spotted an abandoned black box and raised an alarm. 

 Calcutta: Medical College and Hospital has set up a five-member committee to probe the clash between students on the hospital premises on July 10. The brawl was sparked by the admission of a physically handicapped candidate into the college hostel. 

 Calcutta: Representatives of tea garden planters met labour secretary Ashok Mohan Chakraborty on Wednesday but expressed inability to make a renewed offer of higher daily wages to workers. Over 35 gardens across north Bengal are on strike.




